<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,727,1006]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,871,897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">Identification.</emphasis>
This species was identified by keys, descriptions, and figures by 
<bibRefCitation author="Flint, O. S., Jr." box="[1148,1287,871,897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref5519" refString="Flint, O. S., Jr. (1967) Studies of Neotropical caddis flies, IV: New species from Mexico and Central America. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 123, 1 - 24. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.123 - 3619.1" type="journal article" year="1967">Flint (1967)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Flint, O. S., Jr. &amp; Bueno-Soria, J." pageId="4" pageNumber="582" pagination="29 - 37" refId="ref5744" refString="Flint, O. S., Jr. &amp; Bueno-Soria, J. (1987) Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XXXVI: The genus Calosopsyche in Central America, with descriptions of its immature stages (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae). In: Bournaud, M. &amp; Tachet, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 5 th International Symposium on Trichoptera. Dr. W. Junk, Dordrecht, The Netherlands, pp. 29 - 37. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 009 - 4043 - 7 _ 5" type="book chapter" year="1987">Flint &amp; Bueno-Soria (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. A member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint &amp; Bueno-Soria" authorityYear="1987" box="[583,760,907,934]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Calosopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="continentalis">
<emphasis box="[583,760,907,934]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">C. continentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group (
<bibRefCitation author="Olah, J. &amp; Johanson, K." box="[853,1116,907,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" pagination="1 - 248" refId="ref6386" refString="Olah, J. &amp; Johanson, K. (2008) Generic review of Hydropsychinae, with description of Schmidopsyche, new genus, 3 new genus clusters, 8 new species groups, 4 new species clades, 12 new species clusters and 62 new species from the Oriental and Afrotropical regions (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae). Zootaxa, 1802 (1), 1 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1802.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">Oláh &amp; Johanson 2008</bibRefCitation>
), it is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Flint &amp; Bueno-Soria 1987" authorityName="Flint &amp; Bueno-Soria" authorityYear="1987" box="[151,635,943,970]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Calosopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="continentalis">
<emphasis box="[151,330,943,970]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">C. continentalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Flint, O. S., Jr. &amp; Bueno-Soria, J." box="[338,635,943,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" pagination="29 - 37" refId="ref5744" refString="Flint, O. S., Jr. &amp; Bueno-Soria, J. (1987) Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XXXVI: The genus Calosopsyche in Central America, with descriptions of its immature stages (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae). In: Bournaud, M. &amp; Tachet, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 5 th International Symposium on Trichoptera. Dr. W. Junk, Dordrecht, The Netherlands, pp. 29 - 37. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 009 - 4043 - 7 _ 5" type="book chapter" year="1987">Flint &amp; Bueno-Soria 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Flint &amp; Bueno-Soria 1987" authorityName="Flint &amp; Bueno-Soria" authorityYear="1987" box="[692,1127,943,970]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Calosopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicuspis">
<emphasis box="[692,818,943,970]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">C. bicuspis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Flint, O. S., Jr. &amp; Bueno-Soria, J." box="[827,1127,943,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" pagination="29 - 37" refId="ref5744" refString="Flint, O. S., Jr. &amp; Bueno-Soria, J. (1987) Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XXXVI: The genus Calosopsyche in Central America, with descriptions of its immature stages (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae). In: Bournaud, M. &amp; Tachet, M. (Eds.), Proceedings of the 5 th International Symposium on Trichoptera. Dr. W. Junk, Dordrecht, The Netherlands, pp. 29 - 37. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 009 - 4043 - 7 _ 5" type="book chapter" year="1987">Flint &amp; Bueno-Soria 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, differing from both by the widely forked apex of each inferior appendage.
</paragraph>
